President Trump and Prime Minister Netanyahu had a phone conversation to discuss strengthening the U.S.-Israel relationship and promoting security in the Middle East. They emphasized the importance of military, intelligence, and security cooperation between the two countries. They also agreed to closely consult on regional issues, including addressing the threats posed by Iran. President Trump expressed his commitment to Israel's security and prioritizing the fight against radical Islamic terrorist groups. He also stated that peace between Israel and Palestine can only be achieved through direct negotiations between the two parties. President Trump invited Prime Minister Netanyahu to a meeting at the White House in early February.